Hi <%= @user.name %>,

Welcome to the Sample App! Click on the link below to activate you account:

<%= edit_account_activation_url(@user.activation_token, email: @user.email) %>

<%#
edit_user_url(user)  ->
        http://www.example.com/users/1/edit

edit_account_activation_url(@user.activation_token, ...)  ->
        http://www.example.com/account_activations/q5lt38hQDc_959PVoo6b7A/edit
        This token will be available in the Activations controller edit action as params[:id].

edit_account_activation_url(@user.activation_token, email: @user.email)  ->
        http://www.example.com/account_activations/q5lt38hQDc_959PVoo6b7A/edit?email=foo%40example.com
        The resulting email address will be available via params[:email].
        Email is included as query parameter - it appears in a URL as a key-value pair located after a question mark.
%>
